README.md
     1Рєњ# The only accessible & unstyled & full featured Input OTP component in the Web. Рђд
     3Рєњ### OTP Input for React ­Ъћљ by [@guilhermerodz](https://twitter.com/guilherme_rodz)
    18Рєњhttps://github.com/guilhermerodz/input-otp/assets/10366880/753751f5-eda8-4145-a4b9-7ef51ca5e453
    19Рєњ
    20Рєњ## Usage
    22Рєњ```bash
    23Рєњnpm install input-otp
    24Рєњ```
    25Рєњ
    26РєњThen import the component.
    27Рєњ
    28Рєњ```diff
    29Рєњ+'use client'
    30Рєњ+import { OTPInput } from 'input-otp'
    31Рєњ
    32Рєњfunction MyForm() {
    33Рєњ  return <form>
    34Рєњ+   <OTPInput maxLength={6} render={({slots})  => (...)} />
    35Рєњ  </form>
    36Рєњ}
    37Рєњ```
    38Рєњ
    39Рєњ## Default example
    41РєњThe example below uses `tailwindcss` `@shadcn/ui` `tailwind-merge` `clsx`:
    42Рєњ
    43Рєњ```tsx
    44Рєњ'use client'
    45Рєњimport { OTPInput, SlotProps } from 'input-otp'
    46Рєњ<OTPInput
    47Рєњ  maxLength={6}
    48Рєњ  containerClassName="group flex items-center has-[:disabled]:opacity-30"
    49Рєњ  render={({ slots }) => (
    50Рєњ    <>
    51Рєњ      <div className="flex">
    52Рєњ        {slots.slice(0, 3).map((slot, idx) => (
    53Рєњ          <Slot key={idx} {...slot} />
    54Рєњ        ))}
    55Рєњ      </div>
    56Рєњ
    57Рєњ      <FakeDash />
    58Рєњ
    59Рєњ      <div className="flex">
    60Рєњ        {slots.slice(3).map((slot, idx) => (
    61Рєњ          <Slot key={idx} {...slot} />
    62Рєњ        ))}
    63Рєњ      </div>
      РєњРђд
   136Рєњ## How it works
   138РєњThere's currently no native OTP/2FA/MFA input in HTML, which means people are either going with 1. a simple input design or 2. custom designs like this one.
   139РєњThis library works by rendering an invisible input as a sibling of the slots, contained by a `relative`ly positioned parent (the container root called _OTPInput_).
   140Рєњ
   141Рєњ## Features
   143РєњThis is the most complete OTP input on the web. It's fully featured 
   144Рєњ
   145Рєњ<details>
   146Рєњ<summary>Supports iOS + Android copy-paste-cut</summary>
   147Рєњ
   148Рєњhttps://github.com/guilhermerodz/input-otp/assets/10366880/bdbdc96a-23da-4e89-bff8-990e6a1c4c23
   149Рєњ
   150Рєњ</details>
   151Рєњ
   152Рєњ<details>
   153Рєњ<summary>Automatic OTP code retrieval from transport (e.g SMS)</summary>
   154Рєњ
   155РєњBy default, this input uses `autocomplete='one-time-code'` and it works as it's a single input. 
   156Рєњ
   157Рєњhttps://github.com/guilhermerodz/input-otp/assets/10366880/5705dac6-9159-443b-9c27-b52e93c60ea8
   158Рєњ
   159Рєњ</details>
   160Рєњ
   161Рєњ<details>
   162Рєњ<summary>Supports screen readers (a11y)</summary>
   163Рєњ
   164РєњStripe was my first inspiration to build this library.
   165Рєњ
      РєњРђд
   198Рєњ### Auto tracks if the input has space in the right side for the badge
   200Рєњhttps://github.com/guilhermerodz/input-otp/assets/10366880/bf01af88-1f82-463e-adf4-54a737a92f59
   201Рєњ
   202Рєњ</details>
   203Рєњ
   204Рєњ## API Reference
   206Рєњ### OTPInput
   208РєњThe root container. Define settings for the input via props. Then, use the `render` prop to create the slots.
   209Рєњ
   210Рєњ#### Props
   212Рєњ```ts
   213Рєњtype OTPInputProps = {
   214Рєњ  // The number of slots
   215Рєњ  maxLength: number
   216Рєњ
   217Рєњ  // Render function creating the slots
   218Рєњ  render: (props: RenderProps) => React.ReactElement
   219Рєњ  // PS: Render prop is mandatory, except in cases
   220Рєњ  // you'd like to consume the original Context API.
   221Рєњ  // (search for Context in this docs)
   222Рєњ
   223Рєњ  // The class name for the root container
   224Рєњ  containerClassName?: string
   225Рєњ
   226Рєњ  // Value state controlling the input
   227Рєњ  value?: string
   228Рєњ  // Setter for the controlled value (or callback for uncontrolled value)
   229Рєњ  onChange?: (newValue: string) => unknown
   230Рєњ
   231Рєњ  // Callback when the input is complete
   232Рєњ  onComplete?: (...args: any[]) => unknown
   233Рєњ
   234Рєњ  // Where is the text located within the input
   235Рєњ  // Affects click-holding or long-press behavior
   236Рєњ  // Default: 'left'
   237Рєњ  textAlign?: 'left' | 'center' | 'right'
   238Рєњ
   239Рєњ  // Virtual keyboard appearance on mobile
   240Рєњ  // Default: 'numeric'
      РєњРђд
   293Рєњ## Examples
   298Рєњ```tsx
   299Рєњexport default function Page() {
   300Рєњ  const formRef = useRef<HTMLFormElement>(null)
   301Рєњ  const buttonRef = useRef<HTMLButtonElement>(null)
   302Рєњ
   303Рєњ  return (
   304Рєњ    <form ref={formRef}>
   305Рєњ      <OTPInput
   306Рєњ        // ... automatically submit the form
   307Рєњ        onComplete={() => formRef.current?.submit()}
   308Рєњ        // ... or focus the button like as you wish
   309Рєњ        onComplete={() => buttonRef.current?.focus()}
   310Рєњ      />
   311Рєњ
   312Рєњ      <button ref={buttonRef}>Submit</button>
   313Рєњ    </form>
   314Рєњ  )
   315Рєњ}
   316Рєњ```
   317Рєњ</details>
   318Рєњ
   319Рєњ<details>
   320Рєњ<summary>Automatically focus the input when the page loads</summary>
      РєњРђд
   377Рєњ## Caveats
   382РєњBy default, `input-otp` handles password managers for you.
   383РєњThe password manager badges should be automatically shifted to the right side.
   384Рєњ
   385РєњHowever, if you still want to block password managers, please disable the `pushPasswordManagerStrategy` and then manually block each PWM.
   386Рєњ
   387Рєњ```diff
   388Рєњ<OTPInput
   389Рєњ  // First, disable library's built-in strategy
   390Рєњ  // for shifting badges automatically
   391Рєњ- pushPasswordManagerStrategy="increase-width"
   392Рєњ+ pushPasswordManagerStrategy="none"
   393Рєњ  // Then, manually add specifics attributes
   394Рєњ  // your password manager docs
   395Рєњ  // Example: block LastPass
   396Рєњ+ data-lpignore="true" 
   397Рєњ  // Example: block 1Password
   398Рєњ+ data-1p-ignore="true"
   399Рєњ/>
   400Рєњ```
   401Рєњ</details>
   402Рєњ
   403Рєњ<details>
   404Рєњ<summary>[Setting] If you want to customize the `noscript` CSS fallback</summary>
      РєњРђд
